dellNetFipSnooping.name: dellNetFipSnooping

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

dellNetFipSnooping.description: The Dell Networking OS Private MIB for FIP Snooping feature. This MIB module is for configuring FIP snooping related objects and monitoring related FCoE sessions. Terminologies used in this MIB are defined by the T11 FCoE standard. Refer to www.t11.org. This MIB also supports configuration of the following objects: - Port role configuration to identify FCF facing or FCF connected interface - FC-MAP value used by the FCF operating in FPMA mode

dellNetFIPSAdminMode.name: dellNetFIPSAdminMode
dellNetFIPSAdminMode.description: This enables or disables FIP Snooping on the system.

dellNetFIPSFCMAP.name: dellNetFIPSFCMAP
dellNetFIPSFCMAP.description: This object configures the FC-MAP value on the system. Default value is 0x0EFC00.

dellNetFIPSStatsClear.name: dellNetFIPSStatsClear
dellNetFIPSStatsClear.description: Clear all FIP Snooping statistics in the system. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request.

dellNetFIPSVlanCfgTable.name: dellNetFIPSVlanCfgTable
dellNetFIPSVlanCfgTable.description: A table of the FIP Snooping Vlan configuration entries.

dellNetFIPSVlanCfgEntry.name: dellNetFIPSVlanCfgEntry
dellNetFIPSVlanCfgEntry.description: Represents entry for a FIP Snooping Vlan.

dellNetFIPSVlanAdminMode.name: dellNetFIPSVlanAdminMode
dellNetFIPSVlanAdminMode.description: This enables or disables FIP Snooping on a selected Vlan interface.

dellNetFIPSVlanFCMAP.name: dellNetFIPSVlanFCMAP
dellNetFIPSVlanFCMAP.description: This object configures the FC-MAP value associated with the FIP snooping Vlan. Default value is 0x0EFC00.

dellNetFIPSVlanStatsClear.name: dellNetFIPSVlanStatsClear
dellNetFIPSVlanStatsClear.description: Clear FIP Snooping statistics on this Vlan. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request

dellNetFIPSIntfTable.name: dellNetFIPSIntfTable

dellNetFIPSIntfEntry.name: dellNetFIPSIntfEntry

dellNetFIPSIntfPortModeFcf.name: dellNetFIPSIntfPortModeFcf

dellNetFIPSIntfStatsClear.name: dellNetFIPSIntfStatsClear
dellNetFIPSIntfStatsClear.description: Clear FIP Snooping statistics on this interface. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request

dellNetFIPSSessionENodeMacAddr.description: MAC address of the ENode from which the session originated.

dellNetFIPSSessionLoginType.name: dellNetFIPSSessionLoginType
dellNetFIPSSessionLoginType.description: Type of login requested by ENode.

dellNetFIPSFCoEMacAddr.name: dellNetFIPSFCoEMacAddr
dellNetFIPSFCoEMacAddr.description: MAC address assigned to the VN_Port on the ENode.

dellNetFIPSSessionFCID.name: dellNetFIPSSessionFCID
dellNetFIPSSessionFCID.description: FCID created by FCF for this virtual session.

dellNetFIPSSessionENodeIntf.name: dellNetFIPSSessionENodeIntf
dellNetFIPSSessionENodeIntf.description: Interface to which the ENode is connected.

dellNetFIPSSessionFCFIntf.name: dellNetFIPSSessionFCFIntf
dellNetFIPSSessionFCFIntf.description: Interface on which the FCF is discovered.

dellNetFIPSSessionTime.name: dellNetFIPSSessionTime
dellNetFIPSSessionTime.description: Time elapsed after this successful virtual session is established by ENode with FCF.

dellNetFIPSSessionExpiryTime.name: dellNetFIPSSessionExpiryTime
dellNetFIPSSessionExpiryTime.description: This is virtual connection/session expiry interval. This is used to monitor the status of the session. Session entry is removed when the value reaches 0. This value is reset to 450 secs (5*90secs) every time an associated VN_Port FKA is received from the ENode. This is ignored (marked as NA) if the D-bit is set to one in the FCF Discovery Advertisements.

dellNetFIPSSessionState.name: dellNetFIPSSessionState
dellNetFIPSSessionState.description: This is the state of the virtual session. The state is displayed as TENTATIVE during the process of ENode login to FCF (using FLOGI or FDESC). It displays ACTIVE after ENode and FCF establish a successful virtual connection.

dellNetFIPSENodeTimeSinceDiscovered.description: Time elapsed since the ENode is discovered.

dellNetFIPSFCFVlanIndex.description: FCoE Vlan in which the FCF is present.

dellNetFIPSFCFIntf.name: dellNetFIPSFCFIntf
dellNetFIPSFCFIntf.description: Inteface on which FCF is discovered.

dellNetFIPSFCFAddressingMode.name: dellNetFIPSFCFAddressingMode
dellNetFIPSFCFAddressingMode.description: Addressing mode(s) supported by the FCF.

dellNetFIPSFCFPriority.name: dellNetFIPSFCFPriority
dellNetFIPSFCFPriority.description: This is the priority assigned to FCF. The highest priority value is 0 and the lowest priority value is 255.

dellNetFIPSFCFDbit.name: dellNetFIPSFCFDbit
dellNetFIPSFCFDbit.description: This reflects the value of D bit value provided by the most recently received Discovery Advertisement from the FCF.

dellNetFIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin.name: dellNetFIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin
dellNetFIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin.description: This reflects the value of the A bit provided by the most recently received Discovery Advertisement from the FCF. This provides the information that the transmitting FCF is available for FIP FLOGI/FDISC from ENodes. This is informational and shall have no effect on existing logins.

dellNetFIPSFCFConfiguredFKA.name: dellNetFIPSFCFConfiguredFKA
dellNetFIPSFCFConfiguredFKA.description: FIP keepalive interval (FKA_ADV_PERIOD) in seconds configured on the FCF multiplied by five. For example, if the FKA_ADV period configured on the FCF is 80 seconds, the value of this field is 400 seconds.

dellNetFIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered.name: dellNetFIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered
dellNetFIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered.description: Time elapsed since the FCF is discovered.

dellNetFIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount.name: dellNetFIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount
dellNetFIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount.description: Number of ENodes to which FCF has FCoE virtual connections established.

dellNetFIPSFCFSessions.name: dellNetFIPSFCFSessions
dellNetFIPSFCFSessions.description: Total number of FCoE virtual connections successfully established by the ENodes with this FCF.

dellNetFIPSFCFExpiryTime.name: dellNetFIPSFCFExpiryTime
dellNetFIPSFCFExpiryTime.description: This indicates the timer value in seconds to monitor the status of the FCF. FCF entry and all its associated virtual sessions will be removed when the value reaches 0. This value is reset to 'Configured FKA-ADV' every time a Discovery Advertisement is received from the FCF-MAC.

dellNetFIPSVlanStatsTable.name: dellNetFIPSVlanStatsTable
dellNetFIPSVlanStatsTable.description: A table containing per-port, per-VLAN statistics for traffic received. Separate objects are provided for both the most-significant and least-significant bits of statistics counters for ports that are associated with this transparent bridge. The most-significant bit objects are only required on high capacity interfaces, as defined in the conformance clauses for these objects. This mechanism is provided as a way to read 64-bit counters for agents which support only SNMPv1. Note that the reporting of most-significant and least- significant counter bits separately runs the risk of missing an overflow of the lower bits in the interval between sampling. The manager must be aware of this possibility, even within the same varbindlist, when interpreting the results of a request or asynchronous notification.
